Integer to different formats

int x = 100;
System.out.println(Integer.toBinaryString(x));
Integer.toString(100,8) // prints 144 --octal representation

Integer.toString(100,2) // prints 1100100 --binary representation

Integer.toString(100,16) //prints 64 --Hex representation

HashSet doesn't have a get method. So, if you want to do a get do contains and if true then i.e the get method

String.valueOf(sum - 2) // convert int to string
Integer.parseInt(string) // convert string to int
